| Range low reclaim setup: Altcoins | 

> What and how?
It's my favorite pattern to trade, appearing on the total altcoin market cap chart. 

You wait for the reclaim, buy the range lows, and sell the range highs and above. Invalidation: acceptance below the range low again. 
> 2019
Accumulated Bitcoin after the reclaim. I got caught by the covid crash, but I held on to my setup and stuck to the exposure. It was hard, but not capitulating on a setup and sticking to the plan worked in the end. 

> Same setup, different time frames. 

- 5-minute chart range low reclaim
It would have been easy to hold if this above were a 5-minute chart. It takes not that long—maybe an hour—to invalidate or take off. The downside is only a couple of % max. On the other hand, the upside would also only be around 10%. 
- Weekly chart range low reclaim
Now it's appearing on the weekly, the same trade setup, a range reclaim, and should be played the same. But this time, it's suddenly super hard. Because after the reclaim, we ain't doing a retest within an hour; no, it could take months and months of painful chop. Not with a couple of %, but with a potential 50% plus retraces. On the other hand, the upside is hundreds of %.
> How I'm playing this.

1. Getting in:

I've had three major moments buying Altcoins.

- Once Bitcoin reclaimed the range low, I started buying majors like SOL. I knew Altcoins would likely mirror the Bitcoin chart with a little delay. (check chart 1 in this post)

- Once the Altcoin chart reclaimed the range low.

- Both of these entries are still very profitable. My most recent buying spree is slightly underwater (smaller caps like pups), slightly up on majors (SOL), or around BE. It will depend on the short-term market direction, and I'm okay with that. I started adding the 0.25 reclaim of the range in the first quarter. Now the question is if that will hold; if not, we could have a few more months of downside chop, potentially reaching the range low again.

- Another range low (zone) retest would be another entry opportunity. 

2. Paying yourself
I recognize the downside and how hard it could be to hold on to this chart, so I figured I could A) grow my exposure in the range low and B) pay myself on wins (in dollars). For example, I've been buying SOL well below $30 on my first buying spree. Once I was up 200-300%, I took out 10-20% of the profits in dollars without the intention of putting them back in.

3. Simplify things
- I don't care about tomorrow's or next week's prices. I only care about the chart pattern to play out and playing it properly.
Betting on the direction and executing is hard work. Why would you make it even harder for yourself by including a time frame, other noise, etc.? 
I don't care how this pattern plays out; we could chop months and months and go down much more. I care about finding buy spots within the low range, having an invalidation, and having a target. 

4. MAX PAIN
The Max pain scenario for Altcoins, while not invalidating this setup, would be a fail of the first quarterly range level (the 0.25).

If reclaimed properly, the 0.25 acts as a launch path and starting point for parabolic prices, as shown on the chart below.

But if the 0.25 fails to hold after a reclaim, we're opening ourselves up again to the first quarter's lowest range of this range. After confirming the deviation, the range low again becomes a target until we invalidate this by reclaiming the 0.25 once again.

We're now fighting to hold the support, but if it fails, don't rule out another 3-6 months of chop and more downside for Altcoins.

(see how, in 2019, the 0.25 failed to hold, and we retested the lows again)
TLDR:

- Bullish on Altcoins. I believe Altcoins will mirror the Bitcoin chart, with the lag they always have, and this pattern has a very high win rate for me, especially on higher time frames like this.

1. HTF SCENARIO
Please read the long post I linked here: https://x.com/damskotrades/status/1804773987332792802… for an in-depth look at my crypto cycle views and higher-time frame altcoin plan.

In short, I'm playing the higher time frame range low deviation, and reclaim, just like I did with Bitcoin.

> Wait for the deviation to form and the reclaim.
> Buy the lowest part of the range; range low into its 0.25 level, which is the first quarter. Here, "buy" means getting Altcoin exposure.
> Sell Altcoins in the highest quarter of the range; 0.75 into the range high. Here, "sell" means decreasing Altcoin exposure.
> Increase selling after breaking into price discovery during a parabolic run to eventually scale out fully.

So, again, as you can see below. I'm betting on:
a) this range low reclaim to play out and 
b) Altcoins to follow Bitcoin as they always do on higher time frame moves.

I don't care about how exactly on the lower time frames. I carefully took exposure since it was below the range low (why before the reclaim; Bitcoin already reclaimed, and Altcoins usually follow) and after the reclaim. 
But for educational and potential new entry purposes we will dive one-time frame lower to identify zones of interest, dip opportunities, and potential triggers for an alt season.

2. LTF TRIGGERS AND SCENARIO

So, what do we have here in this Altcoin market cap range? We have a higher-time frame bullish range low reclaim setup and a higher-time frame bullish market structure (higher highs and lows).

However, since this is a higher time frame range, the upside is amazing, but the potential downside, without invalidating our setup, is also significant. A small move toward the range lows could mean months of chop and 30%+ more downside.

I'm not necessarily expecting it, and I won't sell the positions I accumulated (many of which much lower) because that's not how I think one should play a range deviation like this. You buy the lows, sell the highs, and don't flip-flop in between.

However, it's good to acknowledge the probability of another few months of chop and a range-low retest.

It would be very similar to what Bitcoin did in 2019.

Just like how deviations work at the range high and low and get sent to the opposite side of the range, deviations also work on the smaller parts of a big range. 

Deviate below the 0.25 level of the range, and the range low becomes more likely.
2019 Bitcoin:

> Confirm the higher time frame (HTF) range low reclaim and bullish market structure (MS), targeting the range high.
> Rejection at the mid-range.
> Deviation below the 0.25 level and into the range low before heading to our original target, the range high and above. (Please, don't comment "But COVID crash, sir.")

Currently, we have deviated below the 0.25 level. Again, I'm not selling because we're still macro-bullish, and I'm sticking to my HTF range deviation plan.

However, it's good to consider potential scenarios if you are looking for an entry.

As we're currently below the 0.25 level, it could become a bearish retest on the LTF; we could dive again into the lower part of the macro range, such as this bullish demand zone.

In my opinion, this would be a great spot to get in, rather than fully allocating yourself now while we retest it.
But again, I'm not selling to buy back lower. I've been taking profit during this cycle on wins, but with the purpose of just taking it slowly out in case I'm wrong. 

If I had zero Altcoin exposure, I would forget about the lower time frames and buy some positions here since it's on the lower part of the HTF range. It's all about slowly building positions and having a plan for it (like we're making right now, lol).

Another great opportunity and potential trigger would be a reclaim of the 0.25 (first quarter resistance) of this range. 

The 0.25 level often triggers the parabolic stage 5 run towards the range high.

If we can reclaim it and turn the lower time frame market structure bullish again, there's a high probability that this could start a parabolic run and alt season, driving prices into the highs and potentially higher.
I also marked the other 0.25 flip or reclaim events on the chart to show how they start the parabolic runs.

So TLDR:

> HTF Altcoins: bullish, sticking to a macro plan since 2023.
> HTF cycle: bullish, but always take profits on big wins into fiat without intending to reinvest immediately.
> LTF: Great Altcoin buy-the-dip opportunity, in my opinion, at the low-demand range.
> LTF: Great Altcoin trigger could be another reclaim of the 0.25 range level.

Sorry for the long text; it's for educational purposes on how I play a cycle and use a range. Make your own plan, but my DMs will be open for help.

Semi-regularly had people call in threats. 
Multiple times over the years had to evacuate or couldn’t go to school for a day.

Try to convert me to “save me from going to hell.” Tell me I’m lucky that I don’t look Jewish. I stopped fighting back. 
I stopped telling them it hurt me. 
It was one of me vs. all of them and if they told me it wasn’t a big deal, I guess it wasn’t a big deal… right?

I’ve realized over the last few weeks how common this experience is for most American Jews.
Going to school with armed guards in the middle of well established and “safe” parts of America.
Being demeaned but then invalidated if it upset us, learning to brush things off because it was easier than always trying to fight back. 
Being outnumbered constantly, told “well you’re my only Jewish friend but you’re one of the cool ones!”

Now being told, “you’re upset about antisemitism but HOW DO YOU THINK ____ FEEL ABOUT ___ (fill in the blank)”

I talked to a friend recently. His young son currently goes one of the same schools I went to — 14 years since I’ve graduated, it’s still the same. 
Armed guards. Double gated. Occasional threats and protests. 

14 years later… 27 years since I started school and not a single thing has changed.

Jewish children being protested against by grown adults. Being viciously “held accountable” for the actions of a government thousands of miles away where many of us haven’t even been. Constantly told our fear and sadness is invalid. Made to feel like it’s okay for other cultures to have and foster their community but when we do it we have an “underground society” where we “greedily control everything”.

Every single Jewish friend I have knows someone who was personally present, k^lled or captured on October 7th. 
Yet, they aren’t allowed to mourn. They haven’t been allowed to share grief. They have been busy fielding hate messages, comments, and antisemitism. 
Constantly screaming into the void for anyone to care like we all cared and advocated over the last few years for Black lives, Asian lives, gay lives and yes… for many of us even Palestinian lives.

Your Jewish friends are tired.
Not just because of the last few weeks, but because this is a culmination of a lifetime of fighting and worrying about our right to just simply exist. We have all been told, shown, subconsciously programmed into thinking “there are people who do not believe you should be alive regardless of what you do, regardless of where you stand, regardless of how much you contribute.”, and the last few weeks have just confirmed it.

That’s it.

 Wait for FCFS Round if you didn't win the WL

Nothing! Just pay the gas fees as the NFTs are free!

How many NFTs can be minted?

1 NFT/1 wallet.

All those who participated in the Whitelist Campaign with our partners and got the spot will be able to mint.

 What are GTD and FCFS Rounds?

GTD is the guaranteed round. If you secured your whitelist spot, you’ll get the NFT.

FCFS is for any NFTs that are left over in the GTD round. These leftover NFTs can then be minted during this round.

 How can I mint the NFTs if I didn’t participate in WL?

If you don’t have a WL spot, wait for the FCFS rounds.
